message.entry: Invalid data type. First argument must be of type double, single, table, or timetable.
Table variables to operate on must be of type double or single.
Breakpoints must be a vector containing sample point values or a logical vector.
Polynomial degree must be a non-negative integer scalar.
Incorrect number of input arguments. Each parameter name must be followed by a corresponding value.
''DataVariables'' value must be a variable name, a vector of variable names, variable indices, logical values, a function handle, or a vartype subscript.
''DataVariables'' function handle must return a logical scalar.
''DataVariables'' parameter is only supported for table and timetable inputs.
''ReplaceValues'' parameter is only supported for table and timetable inputs.
''SamplePoints'' value must be a double, single, datetime, or duration vector.
The number of elements in the ''SamplePoints'' value must equal the size of the first argument along the first dimension.
''SamplePoints'' values must be sorted in ascending order.
Insufficient data points to determine unique polynomial. Reduce the polynomial degree, increase the distance between breakpoints, or add distinct sample points.
